{
  "stem": "25912.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I know there was an occasion when my mother went to see the president of the Jewish Council, Adam Chernikov, to ask if he could do anything to help my grandmother, because she was getting [INAUDIBLE] that she was elderly.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And she came back very saddened.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She said, I was in that room, where over his desk was a portrait of great-grandfather.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he said to her, I get hundreds of people everyday coming with the same request-- there is nothing I can do.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "At that time, we felt very bitter about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "From my reading of history, there really wasn't very much he could have done.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we came to-- [SIGHS] I think, must have gone on for two or three weeks, the deportations, when on one occasion, a friend who was living, again, in the almshouses, told my mother that the following day, the Germans were preparing an action in that area.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he suggested that my mother and I spend the night with him and his wife.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in the morning, he would take us to the police headquarters, where the families of the policemen were sheltering and supposed to be safe.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That morning, we left about 5-- we got ready about 5 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My grandmother and aunt were already in the workshop, and my mother said-- told me to go and say goodbye to grandmother.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember going in, and grandmother came out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were behind the church when I said, Mommy said to say goodbye.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she handed me a gold bracelet, which afterwards, my mother said had been bought for security as capital.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "She gave it to me and said, take this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I said, Mommy didn't tell me to take anything.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
